  "short-title": "IDS",
  "desc": "Statistics, the science of making inferences and decisions under uncertainty, is becoming increasingly relevant in the modern world due to the widespread availability of and access to unprecedented amounts of data and computational resources. Unlike classical statistics, the need to process and manage massive amounts of data has become a key feature of modern statistics. This aspect of managing and processing data is popularly referred to as \"data science.\""
